file_content.text: Whatever brought you to Balmorra, the Republic's glad it did.
Welcome back. I wanted to be the first to congratulate you.
My team's working on the Barrager now. They're already looking into duplicating the weapon on other worlds.
The Imperials are fleeing in droves, afraid we'll finish before their ships clear the planet. Balmorra's free.
Defeating the Empire is worth any sacrifice.
That's what matters.
Sounds like the Barrager's worth all the power it needs.
That's what matters.
To save a galaxy, you've got to break a few planets.
That's what matters.
We'll try to minimize the Barrager's damage as much as possible. But it's a small price to pay for protection from an Imperial fleet.
Just as I hoped.
If Doctor Carsiri was right, the Republic gave Balmorra a stiff bill.
But at what cost?
When he sees how many worlds Balmorra's sacrifice will protect, he'll think differently.
We'll use the Barrager to make sure the Empire never returns to Balmorra. That's the doctor's legacy.
With the Empire on the way out, all that's left is cleaning up the mess. I'll be out of a job soon.
You secured the Barrager, stormed the Gorinth Brig, freed Sobrik--the Republic is completely in your debt.
The Empire has to learn that independent worlds aren't theirs to take.
This is why we fight.
Balmorra's been an effective lesson. If war breaks out, the Republic will be ready.
Even after the Empire's gone, refugees will need escorts, infrastructure's got to get going again....
Let's settle up now.
You've been compensated--quite well, I might add. The Republic knows gratitude's hard to spend.
There's a lot of work ahead. But Balmorra's free--that's what's important. Good luck to you.
The Imperials still have stockpiles here. We need two squads up on the Gorinth Plateau--you're back.
We're in the middle of final troop deployment. The Empire's lost, but they're attacking on their way out.
I don't think you realize what you've done. If we had the Barrager, the Imperials wouldn't have fired another shot.
The Empire's on Balmorra to win. We're here to help.
Victory isn't the point.
I never lied about my intentions, Commander. You did.
I signed on to protect the Republic--including allies like Balmorra.
I just did my duty.
You wanted to destroy Balmorra for a weapon. You might as well join them.
I wanted to give the Republic the best shot I could at defeating the Empire.
The Empire's been forced off Balmorra. That's what we wanted.
What's the big deal?
With the Barrager destroyed, the Empire will just move on to another world. And we have no defense against them.
Were you there when the Empire attacked Coruscant? They came out of nowhere, and we couldn't do anything about it.
When the Empire invaded Balmorra, I promised myself that it would end here. Can you blame me?
Doctor Carsiri risked his life for Balmorra, not the Republic.
Doctor Carsiri would.
For a scientist, he's got guts. Maybe he can help, if he ever forgives me.
No, but he believed in it. Right up until it got him killed.
I... I know. Fast and easy never won a war. I fooled myself into thinking this could be different.
Excuses, excuses.
You've got your own way of saying things, that's for sure. But it doesn't make you any less right.
I'm glad it was you making the call and not me. When you spend your life fighting, it's easy to forget why.
Our next major offensive is Imperial headquarters in the city of Sobrik. There's a sizable Balmorran resistance set up nearby.
Beke Talrott, the resistance leader, requested our aid, but the satellite system kept us from answering. I'd like to send you.
Anyone fighting the Empire can consider me an ally.
We have the same goals.
Beke's a bit of a patriot--he'll like your attitude.
The more allies we have, the better our chances.
We'll need their aid too.
Exactly. Balmorra's not a member of the Republic, but we're hoping to change that.
The Empire's got everything. The resistance can't be well equipped.
They'll need a soldier.
Don't be so sure. Balmorra's covered in factories, workshops, warehouses....
Good to know someone else is fighting back.
I love a rebellion.
Up until now, they were the only ones.
What's the resistance planning?
To do what, exactly?
They claim they can bring down Sobrik's defenses, but they need someone skilled to lead the way.
I'll see what I can do.
I'll let Beke know you're heading in that direction. He'll be waiting.
I've got to get back to troop deployment. I'm certain we'll cross paths again.
We're gaining more ground every day, thanks to you.
Welcome back. The satellite system's down, and the battle's over.
I've been in some intense ops before, but that... let's just say Bugtown never looked so good.
We're holding the Empire back by the skin of our teeth. Freeing captive civilians wouldn't have been my choice.
There was no alternative.
But what's right isn't always what's best.
The Republic's made up of allies, not buildings.
We gain more this way.
I'll do as I please, got it?
At least we've gained some new allies. Sarkus and the rest of the Hawkeyes volunteered to stay and help.
The Hawkeyes know Balmorra's infrastructure better than anyone. Perhaps they'll make future victories more certain.
Either way, we'd likely be standing in a bombed-out mess if it wasn't for you. You've got my thanks.
There's a lot of Balmorra left. What's your next move?
This fight's not over yet.
Get into more populated areas, start contacting the locals.
No thanks necessary.
I'm going to need more.
Serving the Republic has its rewards. Mountains of credits aren't one of them.
With command down, the Imperials didn't know which way was up. We reclaimed countless Republic and Balmorran defenses.
Leaving those Hawkeyes behind was a difficult choice, but I think it was the right one.
Sarkus took my choice pretty hard.
The Hawkeyes don't.
I noticed. He took the first transport out of here.
The admiral threatened Balmorra before I killed him.
Riserre had this planned.
Admiral Riserre always had a vibroblade behind his back in case you dodged the superlaser in front.
Casualties happen.
It's just unfortunate that civilians had to pay the price of our victory.
You did what was best for the Republic. There's no shame in that.
Entering Imperial-occupied territory is no easy task. I hope you're up to it.
I ask for one specialist, and I get a crack team. Lieutenant Hollis deserves a promotion.
Lieutenant Hollis told me he'd found the best help in the galaxy, but I wasn't expecting a Jedi.
Havoc Squad. I won't ask what you're doing on Balmorra--I'm just glad you're able to help.
So the hero of the Esseles is my backup. I couldn't ask for much better.
I'm Commander Madine. We both know why you're here, so I'll lay out the details.
The Empire's taken control of Balmorra's satellite defense system. It's only a matter of time before they find Bugtown and blast us out of this swamp.
If you know Bugtown's in danger, you should evacuate.
If we stay here, yes.
And lose the only part of Balmorra we've got? Leaving won't solve our problems.
A better position could turn this whole thing around.
Then we should move.
Our ships can't launch without getting shot down, and our troops can't move without ships.
Being quick on the trigger solves a lot of my problems.
So blast them first.
Our first offensive was shot down. Another would be a huge risk, not to mention give away our position.
That's one powerful satellite.
How does it work?
The satellites detect enemies, and orbiting turbolasers blast them apart.
That's news to me.
Need-to-know basis. I don't want morale any lower than it already is.
The Empire's got us cornered. As long as they have that satellite system, they're going to keep Balmorra.
But if we could get control of the satellite system, we could turn it on the Empire and even the score.
The satellite system must have a weakness.
That's a good plan.
All we know is that it's well protected. My scouts and SIS agents can't even get close.
Is that possible?
Anything of the Empire's is better left in ruins.
I'd rather destroy it.
When we can use it to defeat them? Sorry, Master Jedi, but I think that's a little wasteful.
But then you leave the system as a potential threat.
Sounds too risky.
If I'm worth even half my rank, the Empire will never have the chance.
Just destroy it. Short, sweet, simple.
Too complicated.
In order to destroy it, we need to gain control of it--so then what's the point?
My best agent managed to gather some intel, but he never made it back. His ship was shot down.
I need someone to enter Imperial territory, find Agent Jago's downed ship and recover the intel.
How do you know the Empire doesn't already have it?
That intel might be gone.
If the Empire has cracked Agent Jago's encryption, we'd be hearing about it elsewhere. Trust me.
Won't I get shot down too?
We've been using a small Balmorran-controlled shuttle pad to transport our scouts. You'll get there in one piece.
Your troops can't handle a simple recovery mission?
You don't need me for this.
My troops wouldn't make it through the Imperial army and back.
Use this decrypter to verify the intel's contents. Then contact me through the comm station at the shuttle pad.
If your agent's alive, I'll find him.
I'll look for survivors.
I've seen the satellite system at work. Nothing gets past it.
The Force will tell us more than any intelligence can.
I'll learn what I can.
I can make some advance strikes if you think it'll help.
Should I do some damage?
I'll keep my eyes open. Doesn't take SIS training to know the score.
I'll check out the situation.
Try to keep quiet. The longer it takes the Empire to catch on, the better our chances.
Ship, intel, shuttle pad.
This will be a breeze.
I hope you're right, Master Jedi. I'd need some serious reinforcements to rescue you.
If you're as quick with your weapon as you are with your mouth, you ought to do fine.
I'll wait for your comm call. Good luck up there.
Are you authorized to be here? This is a war zone. Move along.
Don't worry, Commander. I made a good living along the way.
No matter your intentions, the Barrager would have destroyed Balmorra.
Sure, dropping your cargo will keep it safe. But then you've got no cargo.
Good intentions, bad idea.
The need was the Republic's, and the honor was mine. Safe journey.
You're right. A soldier shouldn't consider his allies expendable. Maybe an early retirement's in order....
Yes, I can see now just how much damage the Empire did.
This is why we fight.
What's the new plan?
At least I was honest.
You're a hypocrite.
Too late for that now.
This isn't our way.
I'm going to need more.
That's what matters.

That's what matters.
This is why we fight.
This is why we fight.

Let's settle up now.

I just did my duty.

Doctor Carsiri would.
